54 } ----

68 static inline uint64_t ScaleAddrDelta(MCContext &Context, uint64_t AddrDelta) { 0
69 unsigned MinInsnLength = Context.getAsmInfo()->getMinInstAlignment(); 0
70 if (MinInsnLength == 1) 0
71 return AddrDelta; 0
72 if (AddrDelta % MinInsnLength != 0) { 0
73 // TODO: report this error, but really only once. ----
74 ; ----
75 } ----
76 return AddrDelta / MinInsnLength; 0
77 } ----

90 // This is called when an instruction is assembled into the specified section ----
91 // and if there is information from the last .loc directive that has yet to have ----
92 // a line entry made for it is made. ----
93 // ----
94 void MCDwarfLineEntry::make(MCStreamer *MCOS, MCSection *Section) { 0
95 if (!MCOS->getContext().getDwarfLocSeen()) 0
96 return; 0
97 ----
98 // Create a symbol at in the current section for use in the line entry. ----
99 MCSymbol *LineSym = MCOS->getContext().createTempSymbol(); 0
100 // Set the value of the symbol to use for the MCDwarfLineEntry. ----
101 MCOS->emitLabel(LineSym); 0
102 ----
103 // Get the current .loc info saved in the context. ----
104 const MCDwarfLoc &DwarfLoc = MCOS->getContext().getCurrentDwarfLoc(); 0
105 ----
106 // Create a (local) line entry with the symbol and the current .loc info. ----
107 MCDwarfLineEntry LineEntry(LineSym, DwarfLoc); 0
108 ----
109 // clear DwarfLocSeen saying the current .loc info is now used. ----
110 MCOS->getContext().clearDwarfLocSeen(); 0
111 ----
112 // Add the line entry to this section's entries. ----
113 MCOS->getContext() 0
114 .getMCDwarfLineTable(MCOS->getContext().getDwarfCompileUnitID()) 0
115 .getMCLineSections() 0
116 .addLineEntry(LineEntry, Section); 0
117 } ----

166 // This emits the Dwarf line table for the specified section from the entries ----
167 // in the LineSection. ----
168 // ----
169 void MCDwarfLineTable::emitOne( 0
170 MCStreamer *MCOS, MCSection *Section, ----
171 const MCLineSection::MCDwarfLineEntryCollection &LineEntries) { ----
172 ----
173 unsigned FileNum, LastLine, Column, Flags, Isa, Discriminator; ----
174 MCSymbol *LastLabel; ----
175 auto init = [&]() { 0
176 FileNum = 1; 0
177 LastLine = 1; 0
178 Column = 0; 0
179 Flags = DWARF2_LINE_DEFAULT_IS_STMT ? DWARF2_FLAG_IS_STMT : 0; 0
180 Isa = 0; 0
181 Discriminator = 0; 0
182 LastLabel = nullptr; 0
183 }; 0
184 init(); 0
185 ----
186 // Loop through each MCDwarfLineEntry and encode the dwarf line number table. ----
187 bool EndEntryEmitted = false; 0
188 for (const MCDwarfLineEntry &LineEntry : LineEntries) { 0
189 MCSymbol *Label = LineEntry.getLabel(); 0
190 const MCAsmInfo *asmInfo = MCOS->getContext().getAsmInfo(); 0
191 if (LineEntry.IsEndEntry) { 0
192 MCOS->emitDwarfAdvanceLineAddr(INT64_MAX, LastLabel, Label, 0
193 asmInfo->getCodePointerSize()); ----
194 init(); 0
195 EndEntryEmitted = true; 0
196 continue; 0
197 } ----
198 ----
199 int64_t LineDelta = static_cast(LineEntry.getLine()) - LastLine; 0
200 ----
201 if (FileNum != LineEntry.getFileNum()) { 0
202 FileNum = LineEntry.getFileNum(); 0
203 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_set_file); 0
204 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(FileNum); 0
205 } ----
206 if (Column != LineEntry.getColumn()) { 0
207 Column = LineEntry.getColumn(); 0
208 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_set_column); 0
209 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(Column); 0
210 } ----
211 if (Discriminator != LineEntry.getDiscriminator() && 0
212 MCOS->getContext().getDwarfVersion() >= 4) { 0
213 Discriminator = LineEntry.getDiscriminator(); 0
214 unsigned Size = getULEB128Size(Discriminator); 0
215 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_extended_op); 0
216 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(Size + 1); 0
217 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNE_set_discriminator); 0
218 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(Discriminator); 0
219 } ----
220 if (Isa != LineEntry.getIsa()) { 0
221 Isa = LineEntry.getIsa(); 0
222 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_set_isa); 0
223 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(Isa); 0
224 } ----
225 if ((LineEntry.getFlags() ^ Flags) & DWARF2_FLAG_IS_STMT) { 0
226 Flags = LineEntry.getFlags(); 0
227 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_negate_stmt); 0
228 } ----
229 if (LineEntry.getFlags() & DWARF2_FLAG_BASIC_BLOCK) 0
230 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_set_basic_block); 0
231 if (LineEntry.getFlags() & DWARF2_FLAG_PROLOGUE_END) 0
232 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_set_prologue_end); 0
233 if (LineEntry.getFlags() & DWARF2_FLAG_EPILOGUE_BEGIN) 0
234 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_LNS_set_epilogue_begin); 0
235 ----
236 // At this point we want to emit/create the sequence to encode the delta in ----
237 // line numbers and the increment of the address from the previous Label ----
238 // and the current Label. ----
239 MCOS->emitDwarfAdvanceLineAddr(LineDelta, LastLabel, Label, 0
240 asmInfo->getCodePointerSize()); ----
241 ----
242 Discriminator = 0; 0
243 LastLine = LineEntry.getLine(); 0
244 LastLabel = Label; 0
245 } ----
246 ----
247 // Generate DWARF line end entry. ----
248 // We do not need this for DwarfDebug that explicitly terminates the line ----
249 // table using ranges whenever CU or section changes. However, the MC path ----
250 // does not track ranges nor terminate the line table. In that case, ----
251 // conservatively use the section end symbol to end the line table. ----
252 if (!EndEntryEmitted) 0
253 MCOS->emitDwarfLineEndEntry(Section, LastLabel); 0
254 } 0

257 // This emits the Dwarf file and the line tables. ----
258 // ----
259 void MCDwarfLineTable::emit(MCStreamer *MCOS, MCDwarfLineTableParams Params) { 0
260 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
261 ----
262 auto &LineTables = context.getMCDwarfLineTables(); 0
263 ----
264 // Bail out early so we don't switch to the debug_line section needlessly and ----
265 // in doing so create an unnecessary (if empty) section. ----
266 if (LineTables.empty()) 0
267 return; 0
268 ----
269 // In a v5 non-split line table, put the strings in a separate section. ----
270 std::optional LineStr; 0
271 if (context.getDwarfVersion() >= 5) 0
272 LineStr.emplace(context); 0
273 ----
274 // Switch to the section where the table will be emitted into. ----
275 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfLineSection()); 0
276 ----
277 // Handle the rest of the Compile Units. ----
278 for (const auto &CUIDTablePair : LineTables) { 0
279 CUIDTablePair.second.emitCU(MCOS, Params, LineStr); 0
280 } ----
281 ----
282 if (LineStr) 0
283 LineStr->emitSection(MCOS); 0
284 } 0

343 SmallString<0> MCDwarfLineStr::getFinalizedData() { 0
344 // Emit the strings without perturbing the offsets we used. ----
345 if (!LineStrings.isFinalized()) 0
346 LineStrings.finalizeInOrder(); 0
347 SmallString<0> Data; 0
348 Data.resize(LineStrings.getSize()); 0
349 LineStrings.write((uint8_t *)Data.data()); 0
350 return Data; 0

368 void MCDwarfLineTableHeader::emitV2FileDirTables(MCStreamer *MCOS) const { 0
369 // First the directory table. ----
370 for (auto &Dir : MCDwarfDirs) { 0
371 MCOS->emitBytes(Dir); // The DirectoryName, and... 0
372 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1)); // its null terminator. 0
373 } ----
374 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // Terminate the directory list. 0
375 ----
376 // Second the file table. ----
377 for (unsigned i = 1; i < MCDwarfFiles.size(); i++) { 0
378 assert(!MCDwarfFiles[i].Name.empty()); 0
379 MCOS->emitBytes(MCDwarfFiles[i].Name); // FileName and... 0
380 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1)); // its null terminator. 0
381 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(MCDwarfFiles[i].DirIndex); // Directory number. 0
382 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // Last modification timestamp (always 0). 0
383 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // File size (always 0). 0
384 } ----
385 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // Terminate the file list. 0
386 } 0
387 ----
388 static void emitOneV5FileEntry(MCStreamer *MCOS, const MCDwarfFile &DwarfFile, 0
389 bool EmitMD5, bool HasSource, ----
390 std::optional &LineStr) { ----
391 assert(!DwarfFile.Name.empty()); 0
392 if (LineStr) 0
393 LineStr->emitRef(MCOS, DwarfFile.Name); 0
394 else { ----
395 MCOS->emitBytes(DwarfFile.Name); // FileName and... 0
396 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1)); // its null terminator. 0
397 } ----
398 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(DwarfFile.DirIndex); // Directory number. 0
399 if (EmitMD5) { 0
400 const MD5::MD5Result &Cksum = *DwarfFile.Checksum; 0
401 MCOS->emitBinaryData( 0
402 StringRef(reinterpret_cast(Cksum.data()), Cksum.size())); 0
403 } ----
404 if (HasSource) { 0
405 if (LineStr) 0
406 LineStr->emitRef(MCOS, DwarfFile.Source.value_or(StringRef())); 0
407 else { ----
408 MCOS->emitBytes(DwarfFile.Source.value_or(StringRef())); // Source and... 0
409 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1)); // its null terminator. 0
410 } ----
411 } ----
412 } 0
413 ----
414 void MCDwarfLineTableHeader::emitV5FileDirTables( 0
415 MCStreamer *MCOS, std::optional &LineStr) const { ----
416 // The directory format, which is just a list of the directory paths. In a ----
417 // non-split object, these are references to .debug_line_str; in a split ----
418 // object, they are inline strings. ----
419 MCOS->emitInt8(1); 0
420 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_LNCT_path); 0
421 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(LineStr ? dwarf::DW_FORM_line_strp 0
422 : dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
423 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(MCDwarfDirs.size() + 1); 0
424 // Try not to emit an empty compilation directory. ----
425 SmallString<256> Dir; 0
426 StringRef CompDir = MCOS->getContext().getCompilationDir(); 0
427 if (!CompilationDir.empty()) { 0
428 Dir = CompilationDir; 0
429 MCOS->getContext().remapDebugPath(Dir); 0
430 CompDir = Dir.str(); 0
431 if (LineStr) 0
432 CompDir = LineStr->getSaver().save(CompDir); 0
433 } ----
434 if (LineStr) { 0
435 // Record path strings, emit references here. ----
436 LineStr->emitRef(MCOS, CompDir); 0
437 for (const auto &Dir : MCDwarfDirs) 0
438 LineStr->emitRef(MCOS, Dir); 0
439 } else { ----
440 // The list of directory paths. Compilation directory comes first. ----
441 MCOS->emitBytes(CompDir); 0
442 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1)); 0
443 for (const auto &Dir : MCDwarfDirs) { 0
444 MCOS->emitBytes(Dir); // The DirectoryName, and... 0
445 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("\0", 1)); // its null terminator. 0
446 } ----
447 } ----
448 ----
449 // The file format, which is the inline null-terminated filename and a ----
450 // directory index. We don't track file size/timestamp so don't emit them ----
451 // in the v5 table. Emit MD5 checksums and source if we have them. ----
452 uint64_t Entries = 2; 0
453 if (HasAllMD5) 0
454 Entries += 1; 0
455 if (HasSource) 0
456 Entries += 1; 0
457 MCOS->emitInt8(Entries); 0
458 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_LNCT_path); 0
459 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(LineStr ? dwarf::DW_FORM_line_strp 0
460 : dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
461 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_LNCT_directory_index); 0
462 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_FORM_udata); 0
463 if (HasAllMD5) { 0
464 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_LNCT_MD5); 0
465 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_FORM_data16); 0
466 } ----
467 if (HasSource) { 0
468 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_LNCT_LLVM_source); 0
469 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(LineStr ? dwarf::DW_FORM_line_strp 0
470 : dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
471 } ----
472 // Then the counted list of files. The root file is file #0, then emit the ----
473 // files as provide by .file directives. ----
474 // MCDwarfFiles has an unused element [0] so use size() not size()+1. ----
475 // But sometimes MCDwarfFiles is empty, in which case we still emit one file. ----
476 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(MCDwarfFiles.empty() ? 1 : MCDwarfFiles.size()); 0
477 // To accommodate assembler source written for DWARF v4 but trying to emit ----
478 // v5: If we didn't see a root file explicitly, replicate file #1. ----
479 assert((!RootFile.Name.empty() || MCDwarfFiles.size() >= 1) && 0
480 "No root file and no .file directives"); ----
481 emitOneV5FileEntry(MCOS, RootFile.Name.empty() ? MCDwarfFiles[1] : RootFile, 0
482 HasAllMD5, HasSource, LineStr); 0
483 for (unsigned i = 1; i < MCDwarfFiles.size(); ++i) 0
484 emitOneV5FileEntry(MCOS, MCDwarfFiles[i], HasAllMD5, HasSource, LineStr); 0
485 } 0

487 std::pair ----
488 MCDwarfLineTableHeader::Emit(MCStreamer *MCOS, MCDwarfLineTableParams Params, 0
489 ArrayRef StandardOpcodeLengths, ----
490 std::optional &LineStr) const { ----
491 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
492 ----
493 // Create a symbol at the beginning of the line table. ----
494 MCSymbol *LineStartSym = Label; 0
495 if (!LineStartSym) 0
496 LineStartSym = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
497 ----
498 // Set the value of the symbol, as we are at the start of the line table. ----
499 MCOS->emitDwarfLineStartLabel(LineStartSym); 0
500 ----
501 unsigned OffsetSize = dwarf::getDwarfOffsetByteSize(context.getDwarfFormat()); 0
502 ----
503 MCSymbol *LineEndSym = MCOS->emitDwarfUnitLength("debug_line", "unit length"); 0
504 ----
505 // Next 2 bytes is the Version. ----
506 unsigned LineTableVersion = context.getDwarfVersion(); 0
507 MCOS->emitInt16(LineTableVersion); 0
508 ----
509 // In v5, we get address info next. ----
510 if (LineTableVersion >= 5) { 0
511 MCOS->emitInt8(context.getAsmInfo()->getCodePointerSize()); 0
512 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // Segment selector; same as EmitGenDwarfAranges. 0
513 } ----
514 ----
515 // Create symbols for the start/end of the prologue. ----
516 MCSymbol *ProStartSym = context.createTempSymbol("prologue_start"); 0
517 MCSymbol *ProEndSym = context.createTempSymbol("prologue_end"); 0
518 ----
519 // Length of the prologue, is the next 4 bytes (8 bytes for DWARF64). This is ----
520 // actually the length from after the length word, to the end of the prologue. ----
521 MCOS->emitAbsoluteSymbolDiff(ProEndSym, ProStartSym, OffsetSize); 0
522 ----
523 MCOS->emitLabel(ProStartSym); 0
524 ----
525 // Parameters of the state machine, are next. ----
526 MCOS->emitInt8(context.getAsmInfo()->getMinInstAlignment()); 0
527 // maximum_operations_per_instruction ----
528 // For non-VLIW architectures this field is always 1. ----
529 // FIXME: VLIW architectures need to update this field accordingly. ----
530 if (LineTableVersion >= 4) 0
531 MCOS->emitInt8(1); 0
532 MCOS->emitInt8(DWARF2_LINE_DEFAULT_IS_STMT); 0
533 MCOS->emitInt8(Params.DWARF2LineBase); 0
534 MCOS->emitInt8(Params.DWARF2LineRange); 0
535 MCOS->emitInt8(StandardOpcodeLengths.size() + 1); 0
536 ----
537 // Standard opcode lengths ----
538 for (char Length : StandardOpcodeLengths) 0
539 MCOS->emitInt8(Length); 0
540 ----
541 // Put out the directory and file tables. The formats vary depending on ----
542 // the version. ----
543 if (LineTableVersion >= 5) 0
544 emitV5FileDirTables(MCOS, LineStr); 0
545 else ----
546 emitV2FileDirTables(MCOS); 0
547 ----
548 // This is the end of the prologue, so set the value of the symbol at the ----
549 // end of the prologue (that was used in a previous expression). ----
550 MCOS->emitLabel(ProEndSym); 0
551 ----
552 return std::make_pair(LineStartSym, LineEndSym); 0
553 } ----
554 ----
555 void MCDwarfLineTable::emitCU(MCStreamer *MCOS, MCDwarfLineTableParams Params, 0
556 std::optional &LineStr) const { ----
557 MCSymbol *LineEndSym = Header.Emit(MCOS, Params, LineStr).second; 0
558 ----
559 // Put out the line tables. ----
560 for (const auto &LineSec : MCLineSections.getMCLineEntries()) 0
561 emitOne(MCOS, LineSec.first, LineSec.second); 0
562 ----
563 // This is the end of the section, so set the value of the symbol at the end ----
564 // of this section (that was used in a previous expression). ----
565 MCOS->emitLabel(LineEndSym); 0
566 } 0

672 /// Utility function to emit the encoding to a streamer. ----
673 void MCDwarfLineAddr::Emit(MCStreamer *MCOS, MCDwarfLineTableParams Params, 0
674 int64_t LineDelta, uint64_t AddrDelta) { ----
675 MCContext &Context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
676 SmallString<256> Tmp; 0
677 MCDwarfLineAddr::encode(Context, Params, LineDelta, AddrDelta, Tmp); 0
678 MCOS->emitBytes(Tmp); 0
679 } 0
680 ----
681 /// Given a special op, return the address skip amount (in units of ----
682 /// DWARF2_LINE_MIN_INSN_LENGTH). ----
683 static uint64_t SpecialAddr(MCDwarfLineTableParams Params, uint64_t op) { 0
684 return (op - Params.DWARF2LineOpcodeBase) / Params.DWARF2LineRange; 0
685 } ----
686 ----
687 /// Utility function to encode a Dwarf pair of LineDelta and AddrDeltas. ----
688 void MCDwarfLineAddr::encode(MCContext &Context, MCDwarfLineTableParams Params, 0
689 int64_t LineDelta, uint64_t AddrDelta, ----
690 SmallVectorImpl &Out) { ----
691 uint8_t Buf[16]; ----
692 uint64_t Temp, Opcode; ----
693 bool NeedCopy = false; 0
694 ----
695 // The maximum address skip amount that can be encoded with a special op. ----
696 uint64_t MaxSpecialAddrDelta = SpecialAddr(Params, 255); 0
697 ----
698 // Scale the address delta by the minimum instruction length. ----
699 AddrDelta = ScaleAddrDelta(Context, AddrDelta); 0
700 ----
701 // A LineDelta of INT64_MAX is a signal that this is actually a ----
702 // DW_LNE_end_sequence. We cannot use special opcodes here, since we want the ----
703 // end_sequence to emit the matrix entry. ----
704 if (LineDelta == INT64_MAX) { 0
705 if (AddrDelta == MaxSpecialAddrDelta) 0
706 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_const_add_pc); 0
707 else if (AddrDelta) { 0
708 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_advance_pc); 0
709 Out.append(Buf, Buf + encodeULEB128(AddrDelta, Buf)); 0
710 } ----
711 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_extended_op); 0
712 Out.push_back(1); 0
713 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNE_end_sequence); 0
714 return; 0
715 } ----
716 ----
717 // Bias the line delta by the base. ----
718 Temp = LineDelta - Params.DWARF2LineBase; 0
719 ----
720 // If the line increment is out of range of a special opcode, we must encode ----
721 // it with DW_LNS_advance_line. ----
722 if (Temp >= Params.DWARF2LineRange || 0
723 Temp + Params.DWARF2LineOpcodeBase > 255) { 0
724 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_advance_line); 0
725 Out.append(Buf, Buf + encodeSLEB128(LineDelta, Buf)); 0
726 ----
727 LineDelta = 0; 0
728 Temp = 0 - Params.DWARF2LineBase; 0
729 NeedCopy = true; 0
730 } ----
731 ----
732 // Use DW_LNS_copy instead of a "line +0, addr +0" special opcode. ----
733 if (LineDelta == 0 && AddrDelta == 0) { 0
734 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_copy); 0
735 return; 0
736 } ----
737 ----
738 // Bias the opcode by the special opcode base. ----
739 Temp += Params.DWARF2LineOpcodeBase; 0
740 ----
741 // Avoid overflow when addr_delta is large. ----
742 if (AddrDelta < 256 + MaxSpecialAddrDelta) { 0
743 // Try using a special opcode. ----
744 Opcode = Temp + AddrDelta * Params.DWARF2LineRange; 0
745 if (Opcode <= 255) { 0
746 Out.push_back(Opcode); 0
747 return; 0
748 } ----
749 ----
750 // Try using DW_LNS_const_add_pc followed by special op. ----
751 Opcode = Temp + (AddrDelta - MaxSpecialAddrDelta) * Params.DWARF2LineRange; 0
752 if (Opcode <= 255) { 0
753 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_const_add_pc); 0
754 Out.push_back(Opcode); 0
755 return; 0
756 } ----
757 } ----
758 ----
759 // Otherwise use DW_LNS_advance_pc. ----
760 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_advance_pc); 0
761 Out.append(Buf, Buf + encodeULEB128(AddrDelta, Buf)); 0
762 ----
763 if (NeedCopy) 0
764 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_LNS_copy); 0
765 else { ----
766 assert(Temp <= 255 && "Buggy special opcode encoding."); 0
767 Out.push_back(Temp); 0
768 } ----
769 } ----

772 static void EmitAbbrev(MCStreamer *MCOS, uint64_t Name, uint64_t Form) { 0
773 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(Name); 0
774 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(Form); 0
775 } 0
776 ----
777 // When generating dwarf for assembly source files this emits ----
778 // the data for .debug_abbrev section which contains three DIEs. ----
779 static void EmitGenDwarfAbbrev(MCStreamer *MCOS) { 0
780 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
781 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfAbbrevSection()); 0
782 ----
783 // DW_TAG_compile_unit DIE abbrev (1). ----
784 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(1); 0
785 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_TAG_compile_unit); 0
786 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CHILDREN_yes); 0
787 dwarf::Form SecOffsetForm = ----
788 context.getDwarfVersion() >= 4 0
789 ? dwarf::DW_FORM_sec_offset 0
790 : (context.getDwarfFormat() == dwarf::DWARF64 ? dwarf::DW_FORM_data8 0
791 : dwarf::DW_FORM_data4); 0
792 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_stmt_list, SecOffsetForm); 0
793 if (context.getGenDwarfSectionSyms().size() > 1 && 0
794 context.getDwarfVersion() >= 3) { 0
795 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_ranges, SecOffsetForm); 0
796 } else { ----
797 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_low_pc, dwarf::DW_FORM_addr); 0
798 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_high_pc, dwarf::DW_FORM_addr); 0
799 } ----
800 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_name, dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
801 if (!context.getCompilationDir().empty()) 0
802 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_comp_dir, dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
803 StringRef DwarfDebugFlags = context.getDwarfDebugFlags(); 0
804 if (!DwarfDebugFlags.empty()) 0
805 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_APPLE_flags, dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
806 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_producer, dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
807 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_language, dwarf::DW_FORM_data2); 0
808 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, 0, 0); 0
809 ----
810 // DW_TAG_label DIE abbrev (2). ----
811 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(2); 0
812 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(dwarf::DW_TAG_label); 0
813 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CHILDREN_no); 0
814 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_name, dwarf::DW_FORM_string); 0
815 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_decl_file, dwarf::DW_FORM_data4); 0
816 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_decl_line, dwarf::DW_FORM_data4); 0
817 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, dwarf::DW_AT_low_pc, dwarf::DW_FORM_addr); 0
818 EmitAbbrev(MCOS, 0, 0); 0
819 ----
820 // Terminate the abbreviations for this compilation unit. ----
821 MCOS->emitInt8(0); 0
822 } 0
823 ----
824 // When generating dwarf for assembly source files this emits the data for ----
825 // .debug_aranges section. This section contains a header and a table of pairs ----
826 // of PointerSize'ed values for the address and size of section(s) with line ----
827 // table entries. ----
828 static void EmitGenDwarfAranges(MCStreamer *MCOS, 0
829 const MCSymbol *InfoSectionSymbol) { ----
830 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
831 ----
832 auto &Sections = context.getGenDwarfSectionSyms(); 0
833 ----
834 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfARangesSection()); 0
835 ----
836 unsigned UnitLengthBytes = ----
837 dwarf::getUnitLengthFieldByteSize(context.getDwarfFormat()); 0
838 unsigned OffsetSize = dwarf::getDwarfOffsetByteSize(context.getDwarfFormat()); 0
839 ----
840 // This will be the length of the .debug_aranges section, first account for ----
841 // the size of each item in the header (see below where we emit these items). ----
842 int Length = UnitLengthBytes + 2 + OffsetSize + 1 + 1; 0
843 ----
844 // Figure the padding after the header before the table of address and size ----
845 // pairs who's values are PointerSize'ed. ----
846 const MCAsmInfo *asmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
847 int AddrSize = asmInfo->getCodePointerSize(); 0
848 int Pad = 2 * AddrSize - (Length & (2 * AddrSize - 1)); 0
849 if (Pad == 2 * AddrSize) 0
850 Pad = 0; 0
851 Length += Pad; 0
852 ----
853 // Add the size of the pair of PointerSize'ed values for the address and size ----
854 // of each section we have in the table. ----
855 Length += 2 * AddrSize * Sections.size(); 0
856 // And the pair of terminating zeros. ----
857 Length += 2 * AddrSize; 0
858 ----
859 // Emit the header for this section. ----
860 if (context.getDwarfFormat() == dwarf::DWARF64) 0
861 // The DWARF64 mark. ----
862 MCOS->emitInt32(dwarf::DW_LENGTH_DWARF64); 0
863 // The 4 (8 for DWARF64) byte length not including the length of the unit ----
864 // length field itself. ----
865 MCOS->emitIntValue(Length - UnitLengthBytes, OffsetSize); 0
866 // The 2 byte version, which is 2. ----
867 MCOS->emitInt16(2); 0
868 // The 4 (8 for DWARF64) byte offset to the compile unit in the .debug_info ----
869 // from the start of the .debug_info. ----
870 if (InfoSectionSymbol) 0
871 MCOS->emitSymbolValue(InfoSectionSymbol, OffsetSize, 0
872 asmInfo->needsDwarfSectionOffsetDirective()); 0
873 else ----
874 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, OffsetSize); 0
875 // The 1 byte size of an address. ----
876 MCOS->emitInt8(AddrSize); 0
877 // The 1 byte size of a segment descriptor, we use a value of zero. ----
878 MCOS->emitInt8(0); 0
879 // Align the header with the padding if needed, before we put out the table. ----
880 for(int i = 0; i < Pad; i++) 0
881 MCOS->emitInt8(0); 0
882 ----
883 // Now emit the table of pairs of PointerSize'ed values for the section ----
884 // addresses and sizes. ----
885 for (MCSection *Sec : Sections) { 0
886 const MCSymbol *StartSymbol = Sec->getBeginSymbol(); 0
887 MCSymbol *EndSymbol = Sec->getEndSymbol(context); 0
888 assert(StartSymbol && "StartSymbol must not be NULL"); 0
889 assert(EndSymbol && "EndSymbol must not be NULL"); 0
890 ----
891 const MCExpr *Addr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
892 StartSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, context); ----
893 const MCExpr *Size = ----
894 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *StartSymbol, *EndSymbol, 0); 0
895 MCOS->emitValue(Addr, AddrSize); 0
896 emitAbsValue(*MCOS, Size, AddrSize); 0
897 } ----
898 ----
899 // And finally the pair of terminating zeros. ----
900 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, AddrSize); 0
901 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, AddrSize); 0
902 } 0
903 ----
904 // When generating dwarf for assembly source files this emits the data for ----
905 // .debug_info section which contains three parts. The header, the compile_unit ----
906 // DIE and a list of label DIEs. ----
907 static void EmitGenDwarfInfo(MCStreamer *MCOS, 0
908 const MCSymbol *AbbrevSectionSymbol, ----
909 const MCSymbol *LineSectionSymbol, ----
910 const MCSymbol *RangesSymbol) { ----
911 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
912 ----
913 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfInfoSection()); 0
914 ----
915 // Create a symbol at the start and end of this section used in here for the ----
916 // expression to calculate the length in the header. ----
917 MCSymbol *InfoStart = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
918 MCOS->emitLabel(InfoStart); 0
919 MCSymbol *InfoEnd = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
920 ----
921 // First part: the header. ----
922 ----
923 unsigned UnitLengthBytes = ----
924 dwarf::getUnitLengthFieldByteSize(context.getDwarfFormat()); 0
925 unsigned OffsetSize = dwarf::getDwarfOffsetByteSize(context.getDwarfFormat()); 0
926 ----
927 if (context.getDwarfFormat() == dwarf::DWARF64) 0
928 // Emit DWARF64 mark. ----
929 MCOS->emitInt32(dwarf::DW_LENGTH_DWARF64); 0
930 ----
931 // The 4 (8 for DWARF64) byte total length of the information for this ----
932 // compilation unit, not including the unit length field itself. ----
933 const MCExpr *Length = ----
934 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *InfoStart, *InfoEnd, UnitLengthBytes); 0
935 emitAbsValue(*MCOS, Length, OffsetSize); 0
936 ----
937 // The 2 byte DWARF version. ----
938 MCOS->emitInt16(context.getDwarfVersion()); 0
939 ----
940 // The DWARF v5 header has unit type, address size, abbrev offset. ----
941 // Earlier versions have abbrev offset, address size. ----
942 const MCAsmInfo &AsmInfo = *context.getAsmInfo(); 0
943 int AddrSize = AsmInfo.getCodePointerSize(); 0
944 if (context.getDwarfVersion() >= 5) { 0
945 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_UT_compile); 0
946 MCOS->emitInt8(AddrSize); 0
947 } ----
948 // The 4 (8 for DWARF64) byte offset to the debug abbrevs from the start of ----
949 // the .debug_abbrev. ----
950 if (AbbrevSectionSymbol) 0
951 MCOS->emitSymbolValue(AbbrevSectionSymbol, OffsetSize, 0
952 AsmInfo.needsDwarfSectionOffsetDirective()); 0
953 else ----
954 // Since the abbrevs are at the start of the section, the offset is zero. ----
955 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, OffsetSize); 0
956 if (context.getDwarfVersion() <= 4) 0
957 MCOS->emitInt8(AddrSize); 0
958 ----
959 // Second part: the compile_unit DIE. ----
960 ----
961 // The DW_TAG_compile_unit DIE abbrev (1). ----
962 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(1); 0
963 ----
964 // DW_AT_stmt_list, a 4 (8 for DWARF64) byte offset from the start of the ----
965 // .debug_line section. ----
966 if (LineSectionSymbol) 0
967 MCOS->emitSymbolValue(LineSectionSymbol, OffsetSize, 0
968 AsmInfo.needsDwarfSectionOffsetDirective()); 0
969 else ----
970 // The line table is at the start of the section, so the offset is zero. ----
971 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, OffsetSize); 0
972 ----
973 if (RangesSymbol) { 0
974 // There are multiple sections containing code, so we must use ----
975 // .debug_ranges/.debug_rnglists. AT_ranges, the 4/8 byte offset from the ----
976 // start of the .debug_ranges/.debug_rnglists. ----
977 MCOS->emitSymbolValue(RangesSymbol, OffsetSize); 0
978 } else { ----
979 // If we only have one non-empty code section, we can use the simpler ----
980 // AT_low_pc and AT_high_pc attributes. ----
981 ----
982 // Find the first (and only) non-empty text section ----
983 auto &Sections = context.getGenDwarfSectionSyms(); 0
984 const auto TextSection = Sections.begin(); 0
985 assert(TextSection != Sections.end() && "No text section found"); 0
986 ----
987 MCSymbol *StartSymbol = (*TextSection)->getBeginSymbol(); 0
988 MCSymbol *EndSymbol = (*TextSection)->getEndSymbol(context); 0
989 assert(StartSymbol && "StartSymbol must not be NULL"); 0
990 assert(EndSymbol && "EndSymbol must not be NULL"); 0
991 ----
992 // AT_low_pc, the first address of the default .text section. ----
993 const MCExpr *Start = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
994 StartSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, context); ----
995 MCOS->emitValue(Start, AddrSize); 0
996 ----
997 // AT_high_pc, the last address of the default .text section. ----
998 const MCExpr *End = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
999 EndSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, context); ----
1000 MCOS->emitValue(End, AddrSize); 0
1001 } ----
1002 ----
1003 // AT_name, the name of the source file. Reconstruct from the first directory ----
1004 // and file table entries. ----
1005 const SmallVectorImpl &MCDwarfDirs = context.getMCDwarfDirs(); 0
1006 if (MCDwarfDirs.size() > 0) { 0
1007 MCOS->emitBytes(MCDwarfDirs[0]); 0
1008 MCOS->emitBytes(sys::path::get_separator()); 0
1009 } ----
1010 const SmallVectorImpl &MCDwarfFiles = context.getMCDwarfFiles(); 0
1011 // MCDwarfFiles might be empty if we have an empty source file. ----
1012 // If it's not empty, [0] is unused and [1] is the first actual file. ----
1013 assert(MCDwarfFiles.empty() || MCDwarfFiles.size() >= 2); 0
1014 const MCDwarfFile &RootFile = ----
1015 MCDwarfFiles.empty() 0
1016 ? context.getMCDwarfLineTable(/*CUID=*/0).getRootFile() 0
1017 : MCDwarfFiles[1]; 0
1018 MCOS->emitBytes(RootFile.Name); 0
1019 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // NULL byte to terminate the string. 0
1020 ----
1021 // AT_comp_dir, the working directory the assembly was done in. ----
1022 if (!context.getCompilationDir().empty()) { 0
1023 MCOS->emitBytes(context.getCompilationDir()); 0
1024 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // NULL byte to terminate the string. 0
1025 } ----
1026 ----
1027 // AT_APPLE_flags, the command line arguments of the assembler tool. ----
1028 StringRef DwarfDebugFlags = context.getDwarfDebugFlags(); 0
1029 if (!DwarfDebugFlags.empty()){ 0
1030 MCOS->emitBytes(DwarfDebugFlags); 0
1031 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // NULL byte to terminate the string. 0
1032 } ----
1033 ----
1034 // AT_producer, the version of the assembler tool. ----
1035 StringRef DwarfDebugProducer = context.getDwarfDebugProducer(); 0
1036 if (!DwarfDebugProducer.empty()) 0
1037 MCOS->emitBytes(DwarfDebugProducer); 0
1038 else ----
1039 MCOS->emitBytes(StringRef("llvm-mc (based on LLVM " PACKAGE_VERSION ")")); 0
1040 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // NULL byte to terminate the string. 0
1041 ----
1042 // AT_language, a 4 byte value. We use DW_LANG_Mips_Assembler as the dwarf2 ----
1043 // draft has no standard code for assembler. ----
1044 MCOS->emitInt16(dwarf::DW_LANG_Mips_Assembler); 0
1045 ----
1046 // Third part: the list of label DIEs. ----
1047 ----
1048 // Loop on saved info for dwarf labels and create the DIEs for them. ----
1049 const std::vector &Entries = ----
1050 MCOS->getContext().getMCGenDwarfLabelEntries(); 0
1051 for (const auto &Entry : Entries) { 0
1052 // The DW_TAG_label DIE abbrev (2). ----
1053 MCOS->emitULEB128IntValue(2); 0
1054 ----
1055 // AT_name, of the label without any leading underbar. ----
1056 MCOS->emitBytes(Entry.getName()); 0
1057 MCOS->emitInt8(0); // NULL byte to terminate the string. 0
1058 ----
1059 // AT_decl_file, index into the file table. ----
1060 MCOS->emitInt32(Entry.getFileNumber()); 0
1061 ----
1062 // AT_decl_line, source line number. ----
1063 MCOS->emitInt32(Entry.getLineNumber()); 0
1064 ----
1065 // AT_low_pc, start address of the label. ----
1066 const MCExpr *AT_low_pc = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Entry.getLabel(), 0
1067 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, context); ----
1068 MCOS->emitValue(AT_low_pc, AddrSize); 0
1069 } ----
1070 ----
1071 // Add the NULL DIE terminating the Compile Unit DIE's. ----
1072 MCOS->emitInt8(0); 0
1073 ----
1074 // Now set the value of the symbol at the end of the info section. ----
1075 MCOS->emitLabel(InfoEnd); 0
1076 } 0
1077 ----
1078 // When generating dwarf for assembly source files this emits the data for ----
1079 // .debug_ranges section. We only emit one range list, which spans all of the ----
1080 // executable sections of this file. ----
1081 static MCSymbol *emitGenDwarfRanges(MCStreamer *MCOS) { 0
1082 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
1083 auto &Sections = context.getGenDwarfSectionSyms(); 0
1084 ----
1085 const MCAsmInfo *AsmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1086 int AddrSize = AsmInfo->getCodePointerSize(); 0
1087 MCSymbol *RangesSymbol; ----
1088 ----
1089 if (MCOS->getContext().getDwarfVersion() >= 5) { 0
1090 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfRnglistsSection()); 0
1091 MCSymbol *EndSymbol = mcdwarf::emitListsTableHeaderStart(*MCOS); 0
1092 MCOS->AddComment("Offset entry count"); 0
1093 MCOS->emitInt32(0); 0
1094 RangesSymbol = context.createTempSymbol("debug_rnglist0_start"); 0
1095 MCOS->emitLabel(RangesSymbol); 0
1096 for (MCSection *Sec : Sections) { 0
1097 const MCSymbol *StartSymbol = Sec->getBeginSymbol(); 0
1098 const MCSymbol *EndSymbol = Sec->getEndSymbol(context); 0
1099 const MCExpr *SectionStartAddr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1100 StartSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, context); ----
1101 const MCExpr *SectionSize = ----
1102 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *StartSymbol, *EndSymbol, 0); 0
1103 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_RLE_start_length); 0
1104 MCOS->emitValue(SectionStartAddr, AddrSize); 0
1105 MCOS->emitULEB128Value(SectionSize); 0
1106 } ----
1107 MCOS->emitInt8(dwarf::DW_RLE_end_of_list); 0
1108 MCOS->emitLabel(EndSymbol); 0
1109 } else { ----
1110 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfRangesSection()); 0
1111 RangesSymbol = context.createTempSymbol("debug_ranges_start"); 0
1112 MCOS->emitLabel(RangesSymbol); 0
1113 for (MCSection *Sec : Sections) { 0
1114 const MCSymbol *StartSymbol = Sec->getBeginSymbol(); 0
1115 const MCSymbol *EndSymbol = Sec->getEndSymbol(context); 0
1116 ----
1117 // Emit a base address selection entry for the section start. ----
1118 const MCExpr *SectionStartAddr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1119 StartSymbol, MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None, context); ----
1120 MCOS->emitFill(AddrSize, 0xFF); 0
1121 MCOS->emitValue(SectionStartAddr, AddrSize); 0
1122 ----
1123 // Emit a range list entry spanning this section. ----
1124 const MCExpr *SectionSize = ----
1125 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *StartSymbol, *EndSymbol, 0); 0
1126 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, AddrSize); 0
1127 emitAbsValue(*MCOS, SectionSize, AddrSize); 0
1128 } ----
1129 ----
1130 // Emit end of list entry ----
1131 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, AddrSize); 0
1132 MCOS->emitIntValue(0, AddrSize); 0
1133 } ----
1134 ----
1135 return RangesSymbol; 0
1136 } ----
1137 ----
1138 // ----
1139 // When generating dwarf for assembly source files this emits the Dwarf ----
1140 // sections. ----
1141 // ----
1142 void MCGenDwarfInfo::Emit(MCStreamer *MCOS) { 0
1143 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
1144 ----
1145 // Create the dwarf sections in this order (.debug_line already created). ----
1146 const MCAsmInfo *AsmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1147 bool CreateDwarfSectionSymbols = ----
1148 AsmInfo->doesDwarfUseRelocationsAcrossSections(); 0
1149 MCSymbol *LineSectionSymbol = nullptr; 0
1150 if (CreateDwarfSectionSymbols) 0
1151 LineSectionSymbol = MCOS->getDwarfLineTableSymbol(0); 0
1152 MCSymbol *AbbrevSectionSymbol = nullptr; 0
1153 MCSymbol *InfoSectionSymbol = nullptr; 0
1154 MCSymbol *RangesSymbol = nullptr; 0
1155 ----
1156 // Create end symbols for each section, and remove empty sections ----
1157 MCOS->getContext().finalizeDwarfSections(*MCOS); 0
1158 ----
1159 // If there are no sections to generate debug info for, we don't need ----
1160 // to do anything ----
1161 if (MCOS->getContext().getGenDwarfSectionSyms().empty()) 0
1162 return; 0
1163 ----
1164 // We only use the .debug_ranges section if we have multiple code sections, ----
1165 // and we are emitting a DWARF version which supports it. ----
1166 const bool UseRangesSection = ----
1167 MCOS->getContext().getGenDwarfSectionSyms().size() > 1 && 0
1168 MCOS->getContext().getDwarfVersion() >= 3; 0
1169 CreateDwarfSectionSymbols |= UseRangesSection; 0
1170 ----
1171 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfInfoSection()); 0
1172 if (CreateDwarfSectionSymbols) { 0
1173 InfoSectionSymbol = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1174 MCOS->emitLabel(InfoSectionSymbol); 0
1175 } ----
1176 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfAbbrevSection()); 0
1177 if (CreateDwarfSectionSymbols) { 0
1178 AbbrevSectionSymbol = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1179 MCOS->emitLabel(AbbrevSectionSymbol); 0
1180 } ----
1181 ----
1182 MCOS->switchSection(context.getObjectFileInfo()->getDwarfARangesSection()); 0
1183 ----
1184 // Output the data for .debug_aranges section. ----
1185 EmitGenDwarfAranges(MCOS, InfoSectionSymbol); 0
1186 ----
1187 if (UseRangesSection) { 0
1188 RangesSymbol = emitGenDwarfRanges(MCOS); 0
1189 assert(RangesSymbol); 0
1190 } ----
1191 ----
1192 // Output the data for .debug_abbrev section. ----
1193 EmitGenDwarfAbbrev(MCOS); 0
1194 ----
1195 // Output the data for .debug_info section. ----
1196 EmitGenDwarfInfo(MCOS, AbbrevSectionSymbol, LineSectionSymbol, RangesSymbol); 0
1197 } ----
1198 ----
1199 // ----
1200 // When generating dwarf for assembly source files this is called when symbol ----
1201 // for a label is created. If this symbol is not a temporary and is in the ----
1202 // section that dwarf is being generated for, save the needed info to create ----
1203 // a dwarf label. ----
1204 // ----
1205 void MCGenDwarfLabelEntry::Make(MCSymbol *Symbol, MCStreamer *MCOS, 0
1206 SourceMgr &SrcMgr, SMLoc &Loc) { ----
1207 // We won't create dwarf labels for temporary symbols. ----
1208 if (Symbol->isTemporary()) 0
1209 return; 0
1210 MCContext &context = MCOS->getContext(); 0
1211 // We won't create dwarf labels for symbols in sections that we are not ----
1212 // generating debug info for. ----
1213 if (!context.getGenDwarfSectionSyms().count(MCOS->getCurrentSectionOnly())) 0
1214 return; 0
1215 ----
1216 // The dwarf label's name does not have the symbol name's leading ----
1217 // underbar if any. ----
1218 StringRef Name = Symbol->getName(); 0
1219 if (Name.startswith("_")) 0
1220 Name = Name.substr(1, Name.size()-1); 0
1221 ----
1222 // Get the dwarf file number to be used for the dwarf label. ----
1223 unsigned FileNumber = context.getGenDwarfFileNumber(); 0
1224 ----
1225 // Finding the line number is the expensive part which is why we just don't ----
1226 // pass it in as for some symbols we won't create a dwarf label. ----
1227 unsigned CurBuffer = SrcMgr.FindBufferContainingLoc(Loc); 0
1228 unsigned LineNumber = SrcMgr.FindLineNumber(Loc, CurBuffer); 0
1229 ----
1230 // We create a temporary symbol for use for the AT_high_pc and AT_low_pc ----
1231 // values so that they don't have things like an ARM thumb bit from the ----
1232 // original symbol. So when used they won't get a low bit set after ----
1233 // relocation. ----
1234 MCSymbol *Label = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1235 MCOS->emitLabel(Label); 0
1236 ----
1237 // Create and entry for the info and add it to the other entries. ----
1238 MCOS->getContext().addMCGenDwarfLabelEntry( 0
1239 MCGenDwarfLabelEntry(Name, FileNumber, LineNumber, Label)); 0
1240 } ----
1241 ----
1242 static int getDataAlignmentFactor(MCStreamer &streamer) { 0
1243 MCContext &context = streamer.getContext(); 0
1244 const MCAsmInfo *asmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1245 int size = asmInfo->getCalleeSaveStackSlotSize(); 0
1246 if (asmInfo->isStackGrowthDirectionUp()) 0
1247 return size; 0
1248 else ----
1249 return -size; 0
1250 } ----
1251 ----
1252 static unsigned getSizeForEncoding(MCStreamer &streamer, 0
1253 unsigned symbolEncoding) { ----
1254 MCContext &context = streamer.getContext(); 0
1255 unsigned format = symbolEncoding & 0x0f; 0
1256 switch (format) { 0
1257 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown Encoding"); 0
1258 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr: 0
1259 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_signed: ----
1260 return context.getAsmInfo()->getCodePointerSize(); 0
1261 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata2: 0
1262 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata2: ----
1263 return 2; 0
1264 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata4: 0
1265 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata4: ----
1266 return 4; 0
1267 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata8: 0
1268 case dwarf::DW_EH_PE_sdata8: ----
1269 return 8; 0
1270 } ----
1271 } ----
1272 ----
1273 static void emitFDESymbol(MCObjectStreamer &streamer, const MCSymbol &symbol, 0
1274 unsigned symbolEncoding, bool isEH) { ----
1275 MCContext &context = streamer.getContext(); 0
1276 const MCAsmInfo *asmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1277 const MCExpr *v = asmInfo->getExprForFDESymbol(&symbol, 0
1278 symbolEncoding, ----
1279 streamer); ----
1280 unsigned size = getSizeForEncoding(streamer, symbolEncoding); 0
1281 if (asmInfo->doDwarfFDESymbolsUseAbsDiff() && isEH) 0
1282 emitAbsValue(streamer, v, size); 0
1283 else ----
1284 streamer.emitValue(v, size); 0
1285 } 0
1286 ----
1287 static void EmitPersonality(MCStreamer &streamer, const MCSymbol &symbol, 0
1288 unsigned symbolEncoding) { ----
1289 MCContext &context = streamer.getContext(); 0
1290 const MCAsmInfo *asmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1291 const MCExpr *v = asmInfo->getExprForPersonalitySymbol(&symbol, 0
1292 symbolEncoding, ----
1293 streamer); ----
1294 unsigned size = getSizeForEncoding(streamer, symbolEncoding); 0
1295 streamer.emitValue(v, size); 0
1296 } 0

1302 int InitialCFAOffset = 0; ----
1303 bool IsEH; ----
1304 MCObjectStreamer &Streamer; ----
1305 ----
1306 public: ----
1307 FrameEmitterImpl(bool IsEH, MCObjectStreamer &Streamer) 0
1308 : IsEH(IsEH), Streamer(Streamer) {} 0

1311 void EmitCompactUnwind(const MCDwarfFrameInfo &frame); ----
1312 ----

1314 void EmitFDE(const MCSymbol &cieStart, const MCDwarfFrameInfo &frame, ----
1315 bool LastInSection, const MCSymbol &SectionStart); ----

1323 static void emitEncodingByte(MCObjectStreamer &Streamer, unsigned Encoding) { 0
1324 Streamer.emitInt8(Encoding); 0
1325 } 0
1326 ----
1327 void FrameEmitterImpl::emitCFIInstruction(const MCCFIInstruction &Instr) { 0
1328 int dataAlignmentFactor = getDataAlignmentFactor(Streamer); 0
1329 auto *MRI = Streamer.getContext().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1330 ----
1331 switch (Instr.getOperation()) { 0
1332 case MCCFIInstruction::OpRegister: { 0
1333 unsigned Reg1 = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1334 unsigned Reg2 = Instr.getRegister2(); 0
1335 if (!IsEH) { 0
1336 Reg1 = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg1); 0
1337 Reg2 = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg2); 0
1338 } ----
1339 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_register); 0
1340 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg1); 0
1341 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg2); 0
1342 return; 0
1343 } ----
1344 case MCCFIInstruction::OpWindowSave: 0
1345 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_GNU_window_save); 0
1346 return; 0
1347 ----
1348 case MCCFIInstruction::OpNegateRAState: 0
1349 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_AARCH64_negate_ra_state); 0
1350 return; 0
1351 ----
1352 case MCCFIInstruction::OpUndefined: { 0
1353 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1354 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_undefined); 0
1355 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1356 return; 0
1357 } ----
1358 case MCCFIInstruction::OpAdjustCfaOffset: 0
1359 case MCCFIInstruction::OpDefCfaOffset: { ----
1360 const bool IsRelative = ----
1361 Instr.getOperation() == MCCFIInstruction::OpAdjustCfaOffset; 0
1362 ----
1363 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_def_cfa_offset); 0
1364 ----
1365 if (IsRelative) 0
1366 CFAOffset += Instr.getOffset(); 0
1367 else ----
1368 CFAOffset = Instr.getOffset(); 0
1369 ----
1370 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(CFAOffset); 0
1371 ----
1372 return; 0
1373 } ----
1374 case MCCFIInstruction::OpDefCfa: { 0
1375 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1376 if (!IsEH) 0
1377 Reg = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg); 0
1378 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_def_cfa); 0
1379 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1380 CFAOffset = Instr.getOffset(); 0
1381 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(CFAOffset); 0
1382 ----
1383 return; 0
1384 } ----
1385 case MCCFIInstruction::OpDefCfaRegister: { 0
1386 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1387 if (!IsEH) 0
1388 Reg = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg); 0
1389 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_def_cfa_register); 0
1390 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1391 ----
1392 return; 0
1393 } ----
1394 // TODO: Implement `_sf` variants if/when they need to be emitted. ----
1395 case MCCFIInstruction::OpLLVMDefAspaceCfa: { 0
1396 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1397 if (!IsEH) 0
1398 Reg = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg); 0
1399 Streamer.emitIntValue(dwarf::DW_CFA_LLVM_def_aspace_cfa, 1); 0
1400 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1401 CFAOffset = Instr.getOffset(); 0
1402 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(CFAOffset); 0
1403 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Instr.getAddressSpace()); 0
1404 ----
1405 return; 0
1406 } ----
1407 case MCCFIInstruction::OpOffset: 0
1408 case MCCFIInstruction::OpRelOffset: { ----
1409 const bool IsRelative = ----
1410 Instr.getOperation() == MCCFIInstruction::OpRelOffset; 0
1411 ----
1412 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1413 if (!IsEH) 0
1414 Reg = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg); 0
1415 ----
1416 int Offset = Instr.getOffset(); 0
1417 if (IsRelative) 0
1418 Offset -= CFAOffset; 0
1419 Offset = Offset / dataAlignmentFactor; 0
1420 ----
1421 if (Offset < 0) { 0
1422 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_offset_extended_sf); 0
1423 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1424 Streamer.emitSLEB128IntValue(Offset); 0
1425 } else if (Reg < 64) { 0
1426 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_offset + Reg); 0
1427 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Offset); 0
1428 } else { ----
1429 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_offset_extended); 0
1430 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1431 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Offset); 0
1432 } ----
1433 return; 0
1434 } ----
1435 case MCCFIInstruction::OpRememberState: 0
1436 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_remember_state); 0
1437 return; 0
1438 case MCCFIInstruction::OpRestoreState: 0
1439 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_restore_state); 0
1440 return; 0
1441 case MCCFIInstruction::OpSameValue: { 0
1442 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1443 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_same_value); 0
1444 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1445 return; 0
1446 } ----
1447 case MCCFIInstruction::OpRestore: { 0
1448 unsigned Reg = Instr.getRegister(); 0
1449 if (!IsEH) 0
1450 Reg = MRI->getDwarfRegNumFromDwarfEHRegNum(Reg); 0
1451 if (Reg < 64) { 0
1452 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_restore | Reg); 0
1453 } else { ----
1454 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_restore_extended); 0
1455 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Reg); 0
1456 } ----
1457 return; 0
1458 } ----
1459 case MCCFIInstruction::OpGnuArgsSize: 0
1460 Streamer.emitInt8(dwarf::DW_CFA_GNU_args_size); 0
1461 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(Instr.getOffset()); 0
1462 return; 0
1463 ----
1464 case MCCFIInstruction::OpEscape: 0
1465 Streamer.emitBytes(Instr.getValues()); 0
1466 return; 0
1467 } ----
1468 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled case in switch"); 0
1469 } ----
1470 ----
1471 /// Emit frame instructions to describe the layout of the frame. ----
1472 void FrameEmitterImpl::emitCFIInstructions(ArrayRef Instrs, 0
1473 MCSymbol *BaseLabel) { ----
1474 for (const MCCFIInstruction &Instr : Instrs) { 0
1475 MCSymbol *Label = Instr.getLabel(); 0
1476 // Throw out move if the label is invalid. ----
1477 if (Label && !Label->isDefined()) continue; // Not emitted, in dead code. 0
1478 ----
1479 // Advance row if new location. ----
1480 if (BaseLabel && Label) { 0
1481 MCSymbol *ThisSym = Label; 0
1482 if (ThisSym != BaseLabel) { 0
1483 Streamer.emitDwarfAdvanceFrameAddr(BaseLabel, ThisSym, Instr.getLoc()); 0
1484 BaseLabel = ThisSym; 0
1485 } ----
1486 } ----
1487 ----
1488 emitCFIInstruction(Instr); 0
1489 } ----
1490 } 0
1491 ----
1492 /// Emit the unwind information in a compact way. ----
1493 void FrameEmitterImpl::EmitCompactUnwind(const MCDwarfFrameInfo &Frame) { 0
1494 MCContext &Context = Streamer.getContext(); 0
1495 const MCObjectFileInfo *MOFI = Context.getObjectFileInfo(); 0
1496 ----
1497 // range-start range-length compact-unwind-enc personality-func lsda ----
1498 // _foo LfooEnd-_foo 0x00000023 0 0 ----
1499 // _bar LbarEnd-_bar 0x00000025 __gxx_personality except_tab1 ----
1500 // ----
1501 // .section __LD,__compact_unwind,regular,debug ----
1502 // ----
1503 // # compact unwind for _foo ----
1504 // .quad _foo ----
1505 // .set L1,LfooEnd-_foo ----
1506 // .long L1 ----
1507 // .long 0x01010001 ----
1508 // .quad 0 ----
1509 // .quad 0 ----
1510 // ----
1511 // # compact unwind for _bar ----
1512 // .quad _bar ----
1513 // .set L2,LbarEnd-_bar ----
1514 // .long L2 ----
1515 // .long 0x01020011 ----
1516 // .quad __gxx_personality ----
1517 // .quad except_tab1 ----
1518 ----
1519 uint32_t Encoding = Frame.CompactUnwindEncoding; 0
1520 if (!Encoding) return; 0
1521 bool DwarfEHFrameOnly = (Encoding == MOFI->getCompactUnwindDwarfEHFrameOnly()); 0
1522 ----
1523 // The encoding needs to know we have an LSDA. ----
1524 if (!DwarfEHFrameOnly && Frame.Lsda) 0
1525 Encoding |= 0x40000000; 0
1526 ----
1527 // Range Start ----
1528 unsigned FDEEncoding = MOFI->getFDEEncoding(); 0
1529 unsigned Size = getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, FDEEncoding); 0
1530 Streamer.emitSymbolValue(Frame.Begin, Size); 0
1531 ----
1532 // Range Length ----
1533 const MCExpr *Range = ----
1534 makeEndMinusStartExpr(Context, *Frame.Begin, *Frame.End, 0); 0
1535 emitAbsValue(Streamer, Range, 4); 0
1536 ----
1537 // Compact Encoding ----
1538 Size = getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, dwarf::DW_EH_PE_udata4); 0
1539 Streamer.emitIntValue(Encoding, Size); 0
1540 ----
1541 // Personality Function ----
1542 Size = getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr); 0
1543 if (!DwarfEHFrameOnly && Frame.Personality) 0
1544 Streamer.emitSymbolValue(Frame.Personality, Size); 0
1545 else ----
1546 Streamer.emitIntValue(0, Size); // No personality fn 0
1547 ----
1548 // LSDA ----
1549 Size = getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, Frame.LsdaEncoding); 0
1550 if (!DwarfEHFrameOnly && Frame.Lsda) 0
1551 Streamer.emitSymbolValue(Frame.Lsda, Size); 0
1552 else ----
1553 Streamer.emitIntValue(0, Size); // No LSDA 0
1554 } ----
1555 ----
1556 static unsigned getCIEVersion(bool IsEH, unsigned DwarfVersion) { 0
1557 if (IsEH) 0
1558 return 1; 0
1559 switch (DwarfVersion) { 0
1560 case 2: 0
1561 return 1; 0
1562 case 3: 0
1563 return 3; 0
1564 case 4: 0
1565 case 5: ----
1566 return 4; 0
1567 } ----
1568 llvm_unreachable("Unknown version"); 0
1569 } ----
1570 ----
1571 const MCSymbol &FrameEmitterImpl::EmitCIE(const MCDwarfFrameInfo &Frame) { 0
1572 MCContext &context = Streamer.getContext(); 0
1573 const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = context.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1574 const MCObjectFileInfo *MOFI = context.getObjectFileInfo(); 0
1575 ----
1576 MCSymbol *sectionStart = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1577 Streamer.emitLabel(sectionStart); 0
1578 ----
1579 MCSymbol *sectionEnd = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1580 ----
1581 dwarf::DwarfFormat Format = IsEH ? dwarf::DWARF32 : context.getDwarfFormat(); 0
1582 unsigned UnitLengthBytes = dwarf::getUnitLengthFieldByteSize(Format); 0
1583 unsigned OffsetSize = dwarf::getDwarfOffsetByteSize(Format); 0
1584 bool IsDwarf64 = Format == dwarf::DWARF64; 0
1585 ----
1586 if (IsDwarf64) 0
1587 // DWARF64 mark ----
1588 Streamer.emitInt32(dwarf::DW_LENGTH_DWARF64); 0
1589 ----
1590 // Length ----
1591 const MCExpr *Length = makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *sectionStart, 0
1592 *sectionEnd, UnitLengthBytes); ----
1593 emitAbsValue(Streamer, Length, OffsetSize); 0
1594 ----
1595 // CIE ID ----
1596 uint64_t CIE_ID = 0
1597 IsEH ? 0 : (IsDwarf64 ? dwarf::DW64_CIE_ID : dwarf::DW_CIE_ID); 0
1598 Streamer.emitIntValue(CIE_ID, OffsetSize); 0
1599 ----
1600 // Version ----
1601 uint8_t CIEVersion = getCIEVersion(IsEH, context.getDwarfVersion()); 0
1602 Streamer.emitInt8(CIEVersion); 0
1603 ----
1604 if (IsEH) { 0
1605 SmallString<8> Augmentation; 0
1606 Augmentation += "z"; 0
1607 if (Frame.Personality) 0
1608 Augmentation += "P"; 0
1609 if (Frame.Lsda) 0
1610 Augmentation += "L"; 0
1611 Augmentation += "R"; 0
1612 if (Frame.IsSignalFrame) 0
1613 Augmentation += "S"; 0
1614 if (Frame.IsBKeyFrame) 0
1615 Augmentation += "B"; 0
1616 if (Frame.IsMTETaggedFrame) 0
1617 Augmentation += "G"; 0
1618 Streamer.emitBytes(Augmentation); 0
1619 } 0
1620 Streamer.emitInt8(0); 0
1621 ----
1622 if (CIEVersion >= 4) { 0
1623 // Address Size ----
1624 Streamer.emitInt8(context.getAsmInfo()->getCodePointerSize()); 0
1625 ----
1626 // Segment Descriptor Size ----
1627 Streamer.emitInt8(0); 0
1628 } ----
1629 ----
1630 // Code Alignment Factor ----
1631 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(context.getAsmInfo()->getMinInstAlignment()); 0
1632 ----
1633 // Data Alignment Factor ----
1634 Streamer.emitSLEB128IntValue(getDataAlignmentFactor(Streamer)); 0
1635 ----
1636 // Return Address Register ----
1637 unsigned RAReg = Frame.RAReg; 0
1638 if (RAReg == static_cast(INT_MAX)) 0
1639 RAReg = MRI->getDwarfRegNum(MRI->getRARegister(), IsEH); 0
1640 ----
1641 if (CIEVersion == 1) { 0
1642 assert(RAReg <= 255 && 0
1643 "DWARF 2 encodes return_address_register in one byte"); ----
1644 Streamer.emitInt8(RAReg); 0
1645 } else { ----
1646 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(RAReg); 0
1647 } ----
1648 ----
1649 // Augmentation Data Length (optional) ----
1650 unsigned augmentationLength = 0; 0
1651 if (IsEH) { 0
1652 if (Frame.Personality) { 0
1653 // Personality Encoding ----
1654 augmentationLength += 1; 0
1655 // Personality ----
1656 augmentationLength += 0
1657 getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, Frame.PersonalityEncoding); 0
1658 } ----
1659 if (Frame.Lsda) 0
1660 augmentationLength += 1; 0
1661 // Encoding of the FDE pointers ----
1662 augmentationLength += 1; 0
1663 ----
1664 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(augmentationLength); 0
1665 ----
1666 // Augmentation Data (optional) ----
1667 if (Frame.Personality) { 0
1668 // Personality Encoding ----
1669 emitEncodingByte(Streamer, Frame.PersonalityEncoding); 0
1670 // Personality ----
1671 EmitPersonality(Streamer, *Frame.Personality, Frame.PersonalityEncoding); 0
1672 } ----
1673 ----
1674 if (Frame.Lsda) 0
1675 emitEncodingByte(Streamer, Frame.LsdaEncoding); 0
1676 ----
1677 // Encoding of the FDE pointers ----
1678 emitEncodingByte(Streamer, MOFI->getFDEEncoding()); 0
1679 } ----
1680 ----
1681 // Initial Instructions ----
1682 ----
1683 const MCAsmInfo *MAI = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1684 if (!Frame.IsSimple) { 0
1685 const std::vector &Instructions = ----
1686 MAI->getInitialFrameState(); 0
1687 emitCFIInstructions(Instructions, nullptr); 0
1688 } ----
1689 ----
1690 InitialCFAOffset = CFAOffset; 0
1691 ----
1692 // Padding ----
1693 Streamer.emitValueToAlignment(Align(IsEH ? 4 : MAI->getCodePointerSize())); 0
1694 ----
1695 Streamer.emitLabel(sectionEnd); 0
1696 return *sectionStart; 0
1697 } ----
1698 ----
1699 void FrameEmitterImpl::EmitFDE(const MCSymbol &cieStart, 0
1700 const MCDwarfFrameInfo &frame, ----
1701 bool LastInSection, ----
1702 const MCSymbol &SectionStart) { ----
1703 MCContext &context = Streamer.getContext(); 0
1704 MCSymbol *fdeStart = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1705 MCSymbol *fdeEnd = context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1706 const MCObjectFileInfo *MOFI = context.getObjectFileInfo(); 0
1707 ----
1708 CFAOffset = InitialCFAOffset; 0
1709 ----
1710 dwarf::DwarfFormat Format = IsEH ? dwarf::DWARF32 : context.getDwarfFormat(); 0
1711 unsigned OffsetSize = dwarf::getDwarfOffsetByteSize(Format); 0
1712 ----
1713 if (Format == dwarf::DWARF64) 0
1714 // DWARF64 mark ----
1715 Streamer.emitInt32(dwarf::DW_LENGTH_DWARF64); 0
1716 ----
1717 // Length ----
1718 const MCExpr *Length = makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *fdeStart, *fdeEnd, 0); 0
1719 emitAbsValue(Streamer, Length, OffsetSize); 0
1720 ----
1721 Streamer.emitLabel(fdeStart); 0
1722 ----
1723 // CIE Pointer ----
1724 const MCAsmInfo *asmInfo = context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1725 if (IsEH) { 0
1726 const MCExpr *offset = ----
1727 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, cieStart, *fdeStart, 0); 0
1728 emitAbsValue(Streamer, offset, OffsetSize); 0
1729 } else if (!asmInfo->doesDwarfUseRelocationsAcrossSections()) { 0
1730 const MCExpr *offset = ----
1731 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, SectionStart, cieStart, 0); 0
1732 emitAbsValue(Streamer, offset, OffsetSize); 0
1733 } else { ----
1734 Streamer.emitSymbolValue(&cieStart, OffsetSize, 0
1735 asmInfo->needsDwarfSectionOffsetDirective()); 0
1736 } ----
1737 ----
1738 // PC Begin ----
1739 unsigned PCEncoding = ----
1740 IsEH ? MOFI->getFDEEncoding() : (unsigned)dwarf::DW_EH_PE_absptr; 0
1741 unsigned PCSize = getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, PCEncoding); 0
1742 emitFDESymbol(Streamer, *frame.Begin, PCEncoding, IsEH); 0
1743 ----
1744 // PC Range ----
1745 const MCExpr *Range = ----
1746 makeEndMinusStartExpr(context, *frame.Begin, *frame.End, 0); 0
1747 emitAbsValue(Streamer, Range, PCSize); 0
1748 ----
1749 if (IsEH) { 0
1750 // Augmentation Data Length ----
1751 unsigned augmentationLength = 0; 0
1752 ----
1753 if (frame.Lsda) 0
1754 augmentationLength += getSizeForEncoding(Streamer, frame.LsdaEncoding); 0
1755 ----
1756 Streamer.emitULEB128IntValue(augmentationLength); 0
1757 ----
1758 // Augmentation Data ----
1759 if (frame.Lsda) 0
1760 emitFDESymbol(Streamer, *frame.Lsda, frame.LsdaEncoding, true); 0
1761 } ----
1762 ----
1763 // Call Frame Instructions ----
1764 emitCFIInstructions(frame.Instructions, frame.Begin); 0
1765 ----
1766 // Padding ----
1767 // The size of a .eh_frame section has to be a multiple of the alignment ----
1768 // since a null CIE is interpreted as the end. Old systems overaligned ----
1769 // .eh_frame, so we do too and account for it in the last FDE. ----
1770 unsigned Alignment = LastInSection ? asmInfo->getCodePointerSize() : PCSize; 0
1771 Streamer.emitValueToAlignment(Align(Alignment)); 0
1772 ----
1773 Streamer.emitLabel(fdeEnd); 0
1774 } 0

1859 void MCDwarfFrameEmitter::Emit(MCObjectStreamer &Streamer, MCAsmBackend *MAB, 0
1860 bool IsEH) { ----
1861 MCContext &Context = Streamer.getContext(); 0
1862 const MCObjectFileInfo *MOFI = Context.getObjectFileInfo(); 0
1863 const MCAsmInfo *AsmInfo = Context.getAsmInfo(); 0
1864 FrameEmitterImpl Emitter(IsEH, Streamer); 0
1865 ArrayRef FrameArray = Streamer.getDwarfFrameInfos(); 0
1866 ----
1867 // Emit the compact unwind info if available. ----
1868 bool NeedsEHFrameSection = !MOFI->getSupportsCompactUnwindWithoutEHFrame(); 0
1869 if (IsEH && MOFI->getCompactUnwindSection()) { 0
1870 Streamer.generateCompactUnwindEncodings(MAB); 0
1871 bool SectionEmitted = false; 0
1872 for (const MCDwarfFrameInfo &Frame : FrameArray) { 0
1873 if (Frame.CompactUnwindEncoding == 0) continue; 0
1874 if (!SectionEmitted) { 0
1875 Streamer.switchSection(MOFI->getCompactUnwindSection()); 0
1876 Streamer.emitValueToAlignment(Align(AsmInfo->getCodePointerSize())); 0
1877 SectionEmitted = true; 0
1878 } ----
1879 NeedsEHFrameSection |= 0
1880 Frame.CompactUnwindEncoding == 0
1881 MOFI->getCompactUnwindDwarfEHFrameOnly(); 0
1882 Emitter.EmitCompactUnwind(Frame); 0
1883 } ----
1884 } ----
1885 ----
1886 // Compact unwind information can be emitted in the eh_frame section or the ----
1887 // debug_frame section. Skip emitting FDEs and CIEs when the compact unwind ----
1888 // doesn't need an eh_frame section and the emission location is the eh_frame ----
1889 // section. ----
1890 if (!NeedsEHFrameSection && IsEH) return; 0
1891 ----
1892 MCSection &Section = ----
1893 IsEH ? *const_cast(MOFI)->getEHFrameSection() 0
1894 : *MOFI->getDwarfFrameSection(); 0
1895 ----
1896 Streamer.switchSection(&Section); 0
1897 MCSymbol *SectionStart = Context.createTempSymbol(); 0
1898 Streamer.emitLabel(SectionStart); 0
1899 ----
1900 DenseMap CIEStarts; 0
1901 ----
1902 const MCSymbol *DummyDebugKey = nullptr; 0
1903 bool CanOmitDwarf = MOFI->getOmitDwarfIfHaveCompactUnwind(); 0
1904 // Sort the FDEs by their corresponding CIE before we emit them. ----
1905 // This isn't technically necessary according to the DWARF standard, ----
1906 // but the Android libunwindstack rejects eh_frame sections where ----
1907 // an FDE refers to a CIE other than the closest previous CIE. ----
1908 std::vector FrameArrayX(FrameArray.begin(), FrameArray.end()); 0
1909 llvm::stable_sort(FrameArrayX, 0
1910 [](const MCDwarfFrameInfo &X, const MCDwarfFrameInfo &Y) { 0
1911 return CIEKey(X) < CIEKey(Y); 0
1912 }); ----
1913 for (auto I = FrameArrayX.begin(), E = FrameArrayX.end(); I != E;) { 0
1914 const MCDwarfFrameInfo &Frame = *I; 0
1915 ++I; 0
1916 if (CanOmitDwarf && Frame.CompactUnwindEncoding != 0
1917 MOFI->getCompactUnwindDwarfEHFrameOnly() && IsEH) 0
1918 // CIEs and FDEs can be emitted in either the eh_frame section or the ----
1919 // debug_frame section, on some platforms (e.g. AArch64) the target object ----
1920 // file supports emitting a compact_unwind section without an associated ----
1921 // eh_frame section. If the eh_frame section is not needed, and the ----
1922 // location where the CIEs and FDEs are to be emitted is the eh_frame ----
1923 // section, do not emit anything. ----
1924 continue; 0
1925 ----
1926 CIEKey Key(Frame); 0
1927 const MCSymbol *&CIEStart = IsEH ? CIEStarts[Key] : DummyDebugKey; 0
1928 if (!CIEStart) 0
1929 CIEStart = &Emitter.EmitCIE(Frame); 0
1930 ----
1931 Emitter.EmitFDE(*CIEStart, Frame, I == E, *SectionStart); 0
1932 } ----
1933 } 0

1935 void MCDwarfFrameEmitter::encodeAdvanceLoc(MCContext &Context, 0
1936 uint64_t AddrDelta, ----
1937 SmallVectorImpl &Out) { ----
1938 // Scale the address delta by the minimum instruction length. ----
1939 AddrDelta = ScaleAddrDelta(Context, AddrDelta); 0
1940 if (AddrDelta == 0) 0
1941 return; 0
1942 ----
1943 support::endianness E = ----
1944 Context.getAsmInfo()->isLittleEndian() ? support::little : support::big; 0
1945 ----
1946 if (isUIntN(6, AddrDelta)) { 0
1947 uint8_t Opcode = dwarf::DW_CFA_advance_loc | AddrDelta; 0
1948 Out.push_back(Opcode); 0
1949 } else if (isUInt<8>(AddrDelta)) { 0
1950 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_CFA_advance_loc1); 0
1951 Out.push_back(AddrDelta); 0
1952 } else if (isUInt<16>(AddrDelta)) { 0
1953 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_CFA_advance_loc2); 0
1954 support::endian::write(Out, AddrDelta, E); 0
1955 } else { ----
1956 assert(isUInt<32>(AddrDelta)); 0
1957 Out.push_back(dwarf::DW_CFA_advance_loc4); 0
1958 support::endian::write(Out, AddrDelta, E); 0
1959 } ----
1960 } ----
